SIMPLE: wrangle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrangle
<hw>Wran"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Wrangled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Wrangling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wranglen</ets> to wrestle. See <er>Wrong</er>,
<er>Wring</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To argue; to debate; to dispute.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dispute angrily; to quarrel peevishly and
noisily; to brawl; to altercate.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In spite of occasional
<xex>wranglings</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For a score of kingdoms you should <qex>wrangle</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He did not know what it was to <qex>wrangle</qex> on indifferent
points.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrangle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wrangle
<hw>Wran"gle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To involve in a quarrel or
dispute; to embroil.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp.
Sanderson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrangle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wrangle
<hw>Wran"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An angry dispute; a
noisy quarrel; a squabble; an altercation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Altercation; bickering; brawl; jar; jangle;
contest; controversy. See <er>Altercation</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrangler</ent>⟦br⟧
